'''theatre'''  (''plural:'' [[theatres]])
# (''Commonwealth English''): A live [[performance]] or the production thereof.
# (''Commonwealth English''): A place or [[building]], consisting of a [[stage]] and seating, in which an [[audience]] gathers to watch [[play]]s, [[movie]]s, speechs or other public ceremonies.
# A region and time of major historical significance, usually regarding warfare.
#: ''His grandfather was in the Pacific '''theatre''' during the war.''
